review_blob: pours a nice brown with a little ruby when held up to light. strong aroma of candi sugar. it also tastes exactly like dark candi sugar rocks. not enough spicy yeast profile. a little too sweet for my tastes. matilda was awesome, but if i want a strong dark ill go for some chimay blue.

pours cloudy golden with decent head retention. very nice light citrus aroma, there is almost a slight grassy aroma. great spicy yeast profile. light mouthfeel. definitely doesnt look as strong as it is.
this beer looks amazing in a goblet, it is a nice amber color. great spicy clove aroma and flavor. overall a great american made belgian-style brew.

It looks nice in the glass. I was expecting a hoppy aroma when I opened the bottle, but I got a very malty aroma instead. The malt comes through in the taste a lot too, as a very caramel flavor. More hops to balance out the sweetness would make this beer a lot better. The mouthfeel is nice though. 

As someone stated in another review, this seems to be more of an ESB. I was not expecting an English Style IPA. For the price its not too bad, just not what I was expecting.
beer_name: Sea Dog (Old East) India Pale Ale
